The paper describes a method for generating test queries and relevance judgments for entity-relationship (E-R) search experiments, and introduces the RELink Framework for E-R retrieval. This work is relevant to information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) research, as well as natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) for E-R extraction and indexing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.DB (Databases), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
